41// supported = version || vertexExt
42static inline SupportRequirement VersionOrExts(GLuint major,
43 GLuint minor,
44 const std::string &versionExt)
45{
46 SupportRequirement requirement;
47 requirement.version.major = major;
48 requirement.version.minor = minor;
49 angle::SplitStringAlongWhitespace(versionExt, &requirement.versionExtensions);
50 return requirement;
51}
52
53// supported = requiredExt && (version || requiredWithoutVersionExt)
54static inline SupportRequirement ExtAndVersionOrExt(const std::string &requiredExt,
55 GLuint major,
56 GLuint minor,
57 const std::string &requiredWithoutVersionExt)
58{
59 SupportRequirement requirement;
60 requirement.requiredExtensions.resize(1);
61 angle::SplitStringAlongWhitespace(requiredExt, &requirement.requiredExtensions[0]);
62 requirement.version.major = major;
63 requirement.version.minor = minor;
64 angle::SplitStringAlongWhitespace(requiredWithoutVersionExt, &requirement.versionExtensions);
65 return requirement;
66}
67
68// supported = version
69static inline SupportRequirement VersionOnly(GLuint major, GLuint minor)
70{
71 SupportRequirement requirement;
72 requirement.version.major = major;
73 requirement.version.minor = minor;
74 return requirement;
75}
76
77// supported = any one of sets in exts
78static inline SupportRequirement ExtsOnly(const std::vector<std::string> &exts)
79{
80 SupportRequirement requirement;
81 requirement.version.major = 0;
82 requirement.version.minor = 0;
83 requirement.requiredExtensions.resize(exts.size());
84 for (size_t i = 0; i < exts.size(); i++)
85 {
86 angle::SplitStringAlongWhitespace(exts[i], &requirement.requiredExtensions[i]);
87 }
88 return requirement;
89}
90
91// supported = ext
92static inline SupportRequirement ExtsOnly(const std::string &ext)
93{
94 return ExtsOnly(std::vector<std::string>({ext}));
95}
96
97// supported = ext1 || ext2
98static inline SupportRequirement ExtsOnly(const std::string &ext1, const std::string &ext2)
99{
100 return ExtsOnly(std::vector<std::string>({ext1, ext2}));
101}
102
103// supported = true
104static inline SupportRequirement AlwaysSupported()
105{
106 SupportRequirement requirement;
107 requirement.version.major = 0;
108 requirement.version.minor = 0;
109 return requirement;
110}
111
112// supported = false
113static inline SupportRequirement NeverSupported()
114{
115 SupportRequirement requirement;
116 requirement.version.major = std::numeric_limits<GLuint>::max();
117 requirement.version.minor = std::numeric_limits<GLuint>::max();
118 return requirement;
119}

121struct InternalFormatInfo

124 InternalFormat glInfo;
125};

127typedef std::pair<GLenum, InternalFormatInfo> InternalFormatInfoPair;

130// A helper function to insert data into the format map with fewer characters.
131static inline void InsertFormatMapping(InternalFormatInfoMap *map,
132 GLenum internalFormat,
133 const SupportRequirement &desktopTexture,
134 const SupportRequirement &desktopFilter,
135 const SupportRequirement &desktopRender,
136 const SupportRequirement &esTexture,
137 const SupportRequirement &esFilter,
138 const SupportRequirement &esTextureAttachment,
139 const SupportRequirement &esRenderbufferAttachment)
140{
141 InternalFormatInfo formatInfo;
142 formatInfo.glInfo.texture = desktopTexture;
143 formatInfo.glInfo.filter = desktopFilter;
144 // No difference spotted yet in Desktop GL texture attachment and renderbuffer capabilities
145 formatInfo.glInfo.textureAttachment = desktopRender;
146 formatInfo.glInfo.renderbuffer = desktopRender;
147 formatInfo.glesInfo.texture = esTexture;
148 formatInfo.glesInfo.filter = esFilter;
149 formatInfo.glesInfo.textureAttachment = esTextureAttachment;
150 formatInfo.glesInfo.renderbuffer = esRenderbufferAttachment;
151 map->insert(std::make_pair(internalFormat, formatInfo));
152}

154// Note 1: This map is used to determine extensions support, which is based on checking support for
155// sized formats (this is ANGLE implementation limitation - D3D backend supports only sized formats)
156// In order to determine support for extensions which introduce unsized formats, this map would say
157// that a corresponding sized format is supported, instead. Thus, if this map says that a sized
158// format is supported, this means that either the actual sized format or a corresponding unsized
159// format is supported by the native driver.
160// For example, GL_EXT_texture_rg provides support for RED_EXT format with UNSIGNED_BYTE type.
161// Therefore, DetermineRGTextureSupport checks for GL_R8 support. Therefore this map says that
162// GL_R8 (and not RED_EXT) is supported if GL_EXT_texture_rg is available. GL_R8 itself
163// is supported in ES3, thus the combined condition is VersionOrExts(3, 0, "GL_EXT_texture_rg").
164//
165// Note 2: Texture Attachment support is checked also by SupportsNativeRendering().
166// Unsized formats appear in this map for this reason. The assumption is
167// that SupportsNativeRendering() will not check sized formats in the ES2 frontend
168// and the information in unsized formats is correct, and not merged like for sized formats.
169// In the ES3 frontend, it could happen that SupportsNativeRendering() would be wrong,
170// but this will be mitigated by fall back to CPU-readback in TextureGL::copySubTextureHelper().
171//
172// Note 3: Because creating renderbuffers with unsized formats is impossible,
173// the value of renderbuffer support is actually correct for the sized formats.
174//
175// Note 4: To determine whether a format is filterable, one must check both "Filter" and "Texture"
176// support, like it is done in GenerateTextureFormatCaps().
177// On the other hand, "Texture Attachment" support formula is self-contained.
178//
179// TODO(ynovikov): http://anglebug.com/2846 Verify support fields of BGRA, depth, stencil and
180// compressed formats, and all formats for Desktop GL.

429const InternalFormat &GetInternalFormatInfo(GLenum internalFormat, StandardGL standard)
430{
431 const InternalFormatInfoMap &formatMap = GetInternalFormatMap();
432 InternalFormatInfoMap::const_iterator iter = formatMap.find(internalFormat);
433 if (iter != formatMap.end())
434 {
435 const InternalFormatInfo &info = iter->second;
436 switch (standard)
437 {
438 case STANDARD_GL_ES:
439 return info.glesInfo;
440 case STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP:
441 return info.glInfo;
442 default:
443 UNREACHABLE();
444 break;
445 }
446 }
447
448 static const angle::base::NoDestructor<InternalFormat> defaultInternalFormat;
449 return *defaultInternalFormat;
450}

452static bool IsLUMAFormat(GLenum format)
453{
454 return (format == GL_LUMINANCE || format == GL_ALPHA || format == GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA);
455}
456
457static GLenum EmulateLUMAFormat(const GLenum format)
458{
459 // This is needed separately from EmulateLUMA because some format/type combinations that come in
460 // to GetNativeFormat don't have entries in the internal format map.
461
462 ASSERT(IsLUMAFormat(format));
463
464 if (format == GL_LUMINANCE || format == GL_ALPHA)
465 return GL_RED;
466
467 return GL_RG;
468}
469
470static const gl::InternalFormat &EmulateLUMA(const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat)
471{
472 ASSERT(IsLUMAFormat(internalFormat.format));
473
474 // Work around deprecated luminance/alpha formats in the OpenGL core profile, and OpenGL ES 3.0
475 // and greater, by backing them with R or RG textures.
476 return gl::GetInternalFormatInfo(EmulateLUMAFormat(internalFormat.format), internalFormat.type);
477}

479static GLenum GetNativeInternalFormat(const FunctionsGL *functions,
480 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
481 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat)
482{
483 GLenum result = internalFormat.internalFormat;
484
485 if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP)
486 {
487 // Use sized internal formats whenever possible to guarantee the requested precision.
488 // On Desktop GL, passing an internal format of GL_RGBA will generate a GL_RGBA8 texture
489 // even if the provided type is GL_FLOAT.
490 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
491
492 if (features.avoid1BitAlphaTextureFormats.enabled && internalFormat.alphaBits == 1)
493 {
494 // Use an 8-bit format instead
495 result = GL_RGBA8;
496 }
497
498 if (internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat == GL_RGBA4 &&
499 (features.rgba4IsNotSupportedForColorRendering.enabled ||
500 features.promotePackedFormatsTo8BitPerChannel.enabled))
501 {
502 // Use an 8-bit format instead
503 result = GL_RGBA8;
504 }
505
506 if (internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat == GL_RGB565 &&
507 ((!functions->isAtLeastGL(gl::Version(4, 1)) &&
508 !functions->hasGLExtension("GL_ARB_ES2_compatibility")) ||
509 features.promotePackedFormatsTo8BitPerChannel.enabled))
510 {
511 // GL_RGB565 is required for basic ES2 functionality but was not added to desktop GL
512 // until 4.1.
513 // Work around this by using an 8-bit format instead.
514 result = GL_RGB8;
515 }
516
517 if (internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat == GL_BGRA8_EXT)
518 {
519 // GLES accepts GL_BGRA as an internal format but desktop GL only accepts it as a type.
520 // Update the internal format to GL_RGBA.
521 result = GL_RGBA8;
522 }
523
524 if ((functions->profile & GL_CONTEXT_CORE_PROFILE_BIT) != 0)
525 {
526 if (IsLUMAFormat(internalFormat.format))
527 {
528 result = EmulateLUMA(internalFormat).sizedInternalFormat;
529 }
530 }
531 }
532 else if (functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
533 {
534 if (internalFormat.componentType == GL_FLOAT)
535 {
536 if (!internalFormat.isLUMA())
537 {
538 // Use sized internal formats for floating point textures. Extensions such as
539 // EXT_color_buffer_float require the sized formats to be renderable.
540 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
541 }
542 else if ((internalFormat.type == GL_FLOAT &&
543 !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_float")) ||
544 (internalFormat.type == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES &&
545 !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_half_float")))
546 {
547 // The legacy luminance/alpha formats from OES_texture_float are emulated with R/RG
548 // textures.
549 if (IsLUMAFormat(internalFormat.format))
550 {
551 result = EmulateLUMA(internalFormat).sizedInternalFormat;
552 }
553 }
554 }
555 else if (internalFormat.format == GL_RED_EXT || internalFormat.format == GL_RG_EXT)
556 {
557 // Workaround Adreno driver not supporting unsized EXT_texture_rg formats
558 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
559 }
560 else if (internalFormat.colorEncoding == GL_SRGB)
561 {
562 if (features.unsizedsRGBReadPixelsDoesntTransform.enabled)
563 {
564 // Work around some Adreno driver bugs that don't read back SRGB data correctly when
565 // it's in unsized SRGB texture formats.
566 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
567 }
568 else if (!functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_EXT_sRGB"))
569 {
570 // Unsized sRGB internal formats are unlikely to be supported by the
571 // driver. Transform them to sized internal formats.
572 if (internalFormat.internalFormat == GL_SRGB ||
573 internalFormat.internalFormat == GL_SRGB_ALPHA_EXT)
574 {
575 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
576 }
577 }
578 }
579 else if ((internalFormat.internalFormat == GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT ||
580 internalFormat.internalFormat == GL_DEPTH_STENCIL) &&
581 !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_depth_texture"))
582 {
583 // Use ES 3.0 sized internal formats for depth/stencil textures when the driver doesn't
584 // advertise GL_OES_depth_texture, since it's likely the driver will reject unsized
585 // internal formats.
586 if (internalFormat.internalFormat == GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT &&
587 internalFormat.type == GL_UNSIGNED_INT &&
588 !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_depth32"))
589 {
590 // Best-effort attempt to provide as many bits as possible.
591 result = GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT24;
592 // Note: could also consider promoting GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT / GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT to a
593 // higher precision.
594 }
595 else
596 {
597 result = internalFormat.sizedInternalFormat;
598 }
599 }
600 }
601
602 return result;
603}

605static GLenum GetNativeFormat(const FunctionsGL *functions,
606 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
607 GLenum format,
608 GLenum type)
609{
610 GLenum result = format;
611
612 if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP)
613 {
614 // The ES SRGB extensions require that the provided format is GL_SRGB or SRGB_ALPHA but
615 // the desktop GL extensions only accept GL_RGB or GL_RGBA. Convert them.
616 if (format == GL_SRGB)
617 {
618 result = GL_RGB;
619 }
620
621 if (format == GL_SRGB_ALPHA)
622 {
623 result = GL_RGBA;
624 }
625
626 if ((functions->profile & GL_CONTEXT_CORE_PROFILE_BIT) != 0)
627 {
628 // Work around deprecated luminance alpha formats in the OpenGL core profile by backing
629 // them with R or RG textures.
630 if (IsLUMAFormat(format))
631 {
632 result = EmulateLUMAFormat(format);
633 }
634 }
635 }
636 else if (functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
637 {
638 // Transform sRGB formats to RGB if either the GLES driver doesn't support GL_EXT_sRGB, or
639 // to work around Adreno driver bugs reading back unsized sRGB texture data.
640 if (!functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_EXT_sRGB") ||
641 features.unsizedsRGBReadPixelsDoesntTransform.enabled)
642 {
643 if (format == GL_SRGB)
644 {
645 result = GL_RGB;
646 }
647
648 if (format == GL_SRGB_ALPHA_EXT)
649 {
650 result = GL_RGBA;
651 }
652 }
653
654 if ((type == GL_FLOAT && !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_float")) ||
655 (type == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES &&
656 !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_half_float")))
657 {
658 // On ES 3.0 systems that don't have GL_OES_texture_float or OES_texture_half_float, the
659 // LUMINANCE/ALPHA formats from those extensions must be emulated with R/RG textures.
660 if (IsLUMAFormat(format))
661 {
662 result = EmulateLUMAFormat(format);
663 }
664 }
665 }
666
667 return result;
668}

670static GLenum GetNativeCompressedFormat(const FunctionsGL *functions,
671 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
672 GLenum format)
673{
674 GLenum result = format;
675
676 if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP)
677 {
678 if (format == GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES)
679 {
680 // GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES is not available in any desktop GL extension but the compression
681 // format is forwards compatible so just use the ETC2 format.
682 result = GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2;
683 }
684 }
685
686 if (functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
687 {
688 if (format == GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES)
689 {
690 // Pass GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2 as the target format in ES3 and higher because it
691 // becomes a core format.
692 result = GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2;
693 }
694 }
695
696 if (features.avoidDXT1sRGBTextureFormat.enabled)
697 {
698 if (format == GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT)
699 {
700 // Pass GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT instead to workaround driver bug.
701 result = GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT;
702 }
703 }
704
705 return result;
706}

708static GLenum GetNativeType(const FunctionsGL *functions,
709 const angle::FeaturesGL &features,
710 GLenum format,
711 GLenum type)
712{
713 GLenum result = type;
714
715 if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_DESKTOP)
716 {
717 if (type == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES)
718 {
719 // The enums differ for the OES half float extensions and desktop GL spec.
720 // Update it.
721 result = GL_HALF_FLOAT;
722 }
723 }
724 else if (functions->isAtLeastGLES(gl::Version(3, 0)))
725 {
726 if (type == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES)
727 {
728 if (!IsLUMAFormat(format) || !functions->hasGLESExtension("GL_OES_texture_half_float"))
729 {
730 // In ES3, the luminance formats come from OES_texture_half_float, which uses
731 // HALF_FLOAT_OES. Other formats (like RGBA) use HALF_FLOAT (non-OES) in ES3.
732 // If they're emulated (see above), use HALF_FLOAT.
733 result = GL_HALF_FLOAT;
734 }
735 }
736 }
737 else if (functions->standard == STANDARD_GL_ES && functions->version == gl::Version(2, 0))
738 {
739 // On ES2, convert GL_HALF_FLOAT to GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES as a convenience for internal
740 // functions. It should not be possible to get here by a normal glTexImage2D call.
741 if (type == GL_HALF_FLOAT)
742 {
743 ASSERT(functions->hasGLExtension("GL_OES_texture_half_float"));
744 result = GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES;
745 }
746 }
747
748 return result;
749}
